I"¬<p>Levels of <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/pupil-light-response-stabilizes-luminance-on-retina">perceived light</a> have been shown to inform the circadian <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/neural-activity-is-piano-playing">rhythm</a>. It seems that compounds secreted in the eye in response to light are responsible for this. Blue light appears to particularly drive chemical adaptation in the eye.</p>
